# Escalation — {{agent_id}}

> What happens when this agent encounters an uncaught exception, a
> critical-action failure, or an approval timeout.

## Escalation triggers

The agent escalates when ANY of:

1. **Uncaught exception during wake** — runtime error, network failure,
   unparseable input
2. **Critical-action tool returns failure** — the action was the
   agent's primary purpose for this wake (NOT every L1 fetch failure)
3. **Approval timeout** — agent sent an approval request and operator
   didn't reply within `{{approval_timeout_sec}}` seconds (handled by
   `escalation-router.sh` watchdog in the bash reference impl)
4. **Explicit `escalate(...)` call from agent prose** — agent decides
   on its own that the situation needs human judgment

## Escalation message format (agent-prose path)

When the agent itself escalates (paths 1, 2, 4 above), it composes a
4-part message via `scripts/telegram-send.sh`:

```
ESCALATION — {{agent_id}}
Correlation: <correlation-id>

What I tried: <one-paragraph description of the action>

Why it failed: <root cause if known; "unknown" otherwise>

Options:
1. <option 1>
2. <option 2>
3. <option 3>

Recommended: <option N> — <one-line rationale>

Reply: /resume <correlation-id> <free-text instructions>
   OR  /halt   <correlation-id>
```

## Approval-timeout escalation (router path)

For path 3, `escalation-router.sh` automatically re-pings the
operator:
- Tier 1 ping after `{{approval_timeout_sec}}` seconds
- Tier 2 ping after another `{{approval_timeout_sec}}` seconds
- Tier 3 final ping (ceiling, then silent)

Each tier uses a derived child correlation-id (`<orig>-esc1`, etc.)
to bypass the dedup in `telegram-send.sh`.

## Persistent halt

After an escalation fires, the agent's `last-run.json status` (or
equivalent state file in your runtime) is set to `error`. Subsequent
wakes short-circuit with `wake_outcome: skipped-prior-error` until
`/resume <correlation-id>` lands.

Rationale: avoids repeated cost spend on a known-broken state.

## /resume + /halt grammar

| Reply | Effect |
|---|---|
| `/resume <correlation-id>` | Set `last-run.json status: idle`. Next wake resumes work. |
| `/resume <correlation-id> <text>` | Same + append text to agent's open-items memory |
| `/halt <correlation-id>` | Confirm persistent halt. Escalates one tier higher (if configured) |

## Escalation target

| Channel | Who receives |
|---|---|
| `escalation_chat_id` (env) | {{escalation_target_description}} |
| Fallback to `TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID` | If escalation channel not configured |

